entry.title: Campervan trader found to have ripped off customers for tens of thousands of dollars in 4 year probe

media:group.media:title: Campervan trader found to have ripped off customers for tens of thousands of dollars in 4 year probe
media:group.media:description: His campervans may constantly be breaking down, but Lindsey Michael Simmonds just keeps going. The campervan trader was previously declared bankrupt and then had his company, The Bus Haus, put into liquidation. Yet customers continue to be ripped off for tens of thousands of dollars. Simmonds refused to talk to Fair Go about this, so Fair Go confronted him in Rotorua. It wasn't pretty.

media:group.media:title: HER TURN AT THE TOP
media:group.media:description:
Within the space of a day, Judith Collins went from the highs of the campaign trail to the lows of political limbo. The newly elected leader of the opposition – a woman who has finally achieved her dream job, only to feel side lined during a national crisis. We’re alongside her through this tumultuous week.
Reporter: Rebecca Wright Producer: Kim Peacock Cameras: Rewi Heke, Will Green, Barrington West Editor: Ben Selkirk

media:group.media:title: WHAT A WEEK
media:group.media:description:
At the beginning of this week we had exclusive access to the prime minister as she launched her election campaign. That was Monday, but just 24 hours later – the country was back in lockdown and our coveted community transmission-free status was gone. We’re with Jacinda Ardern as she navigates politics and a pandemic with the opposition hot on her heels.
Reporter: Miriama Kamo Producer: Paul Deady Cameras: Phil Melville, Matt Smith Editor: Bleddyn Parry

media:group.media:title: RUN WITH MATT
media:group.media:description:
Constable Matt Hunt had his whole life in front of him. A promising career in the police, and he was about to run his first half marathon. His future was tragically taken when he was shot and killed in the line of duty. But his best friends don't want him to be remembered for how he died, but for how he lived.. So they're running the Taupo half marathon for him.
Reporter: Matt Chisholm Producer: Steve Butler Cameras: Gary Hopper, Will Green, Rewi Heke Editor: Gareth Pearce, Ben Selkirk
